# X Monitor Module

## Overview
Monitors Elon Musk's X posting activity via XTracker API (Polymarket's official resolution source) and provides strategy-driven alerts for Polymarket tweet count markets.

## Data Sources
- **XTracker API**: `xtracker.polymarket.com/api` - post counts, tracking periods, individual posts
- **Polymarket Gamma API**: `gamma-api.polymarket.com` - market bracket prices

## Architecture
- Backend poller runs every 2.5min for XTracker, 5min for Polymarket
- Strategy engine evaluates 4 strategy templates with per-instance throttling
- WebSocket pushes real-time updates to frontend
- Web Push notifications via pywebpush + Service Worker

## Strategy Types
1. `silent_period` - Alert when no posts for configured hours
2. `tail_sweep` - Alert when bracket already passed and Yes price high
3. `settlement_no` - Alert when gap too large near settlement (buy No)
4. `panic_fade` - Alert when panic Yes buying on unreachable brackets (buy No)

## Key Files
- Backend: `zentrade-backend/app/xmonitor/` (poller, strategy, clients, router, push, database, models)
- Frontend: `zentrade-app/src/app/x-monitor/page.tsx`, `src/components/modules/x-monitor/`
- Store: `zentrade-app/src/lib/xmonitor-store.ts`
- API: `zentrade-app/src/lib/xmonitor-api.ts`
- Types: `zentrade-app/src/types/xmonitor.ts`
- Service Worker: `zentrade-app/public/sw.js`
